OL,3,CJury retires in trial of husband and
OL,4,Cson accused of manslaughter
OL,6,FIt is alleged by the prosecution that
OL,7,Fhusband Morgan and son by another man
OL,8,FHolyoak ` who lived with Mrs Morgan at
OL,9,Fher Calder Avenue home in Whitehaven `
OL,10,F"completely failed to properly take
OL,11,Fcare of her", or at the very least get
OL,12,Fher some help and that they "left her
OL,13,Fto die."
OL,15,FGiving evidence during their trial,
OL,16,FMorgan and Holyoak both said they were
OL,17,Fabiding by wishes they say were
OL,18,Fexpressed by Mrs Morgan that no
OL,19,Fmedical help be sought and provided.
